content: Hi! I've been using Rust for around a year now exclusively for personal projects, but consider myself low intermediate at best. I've never contributed back to the language yet, but since 95% of my Rust-related rage post-conquering-borrowck has been related to intra-crate error handling, I'm extremely interested to a find a way to contribute to this WG

Hi Casey Bailey! I don't think the Error Handling Project Group has a dedicated Zulip stream (yet?), but you can ask in #t-libs where people will probably be able to help you find something interesting you can do to help
we do saul we do :stuck_out_tongue:
and welcome there Casey :smile:
